s. And started to drive [them] to the appell square, and from there we should be taken for evacuation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2180.137","u": "On what story [floor] was it [in the hospital]?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2182.199","u": "It was on...it had no stories."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2185.994","u": "Why through the windows and not through the doors?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2188.690","u": "Because nobody wanted to go."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2190.359","u": "Aha. And?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2191.403","u": "Everyone was reluctant to be evacuated."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2193.926","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2194.528","u": "And they poured water over these people. Nobody wan-...they still did not carry it out, because the people told themselves.... They called to their faces to shoot them."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2204.266","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2204.993","u": "But they did not shoot. I do not know why. And on the next day, the same story. Finally they succeeded. They assembled the people on the appell square."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2216.328","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2217.237","u": "And I went up there, too. And I saw standing there a transport of youths [youngsters]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2223.587","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2223.769","u": "And that was for a reason [?]. They had been selected to remain in the lager. They were not suitable for transport. And so I went over there. I, of course, am young too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2233.830","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2234.465","u": "And I went over and mingled in, and returned to the lager. And these people left on a transport. And this was on Tuesday already. And on Wednesday...that day was the eighth day that we were completely without food. Wednesday morning we heard the shooting on the part of the Germans [?], and at ten o&#39;clock we heard an enemy...enemy alarm [to be sounded on the approach of the enemy]. The Americans had arrived, one American tank, and went back. And by eleven o&#39;clock planes came over. And at three-thirty we were liberated by the Americans. The first Americans had arrived. The Germans had abandoned the lager entirely."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2277.872","u": "When did the Germans abandon the lager?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2280.181","u": "They left at one o&#39;clock in the afternoon."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2282.029","u": "What did they say?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2283.736","u": "Nothing. We only saw them leaving the watchtowers. It was so. Afterwards we dis-...dis-...discovered...heard that from Weimar the lager commander had telephoned to demolish the lager, [he telephoned] one hour after the liberation. He did not know yet that the lager had already been liberated. It was at half past four. So the lager elder -- he was a prisoner -- answered him, &#39;Yes, yes, we will demolish their heads.&#39; If we had not been liberated an hour before, they would have demolished the lager."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2319.572","u": "What did he answer him?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2321.631","u": "That [now] he should already telephone to Lord God and not to us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2326.101","u": "Aha. Nu?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2328.527","u": "And thus we were liberated. And so, [about] this liberation, people had imagined whole stories, great happiness, but many people also died after the liberation, because they received very fat food. And they completely ruined their stomachs. They got stomach aches, and they died from that, too."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2348.996","u": "Yes. And then where..."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2352.855","u": "And then I was taken away to a youth block, and there I was for a certain time. There I became sick with spotted typhus."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2362.741","u": "After the liberation you had spotted typhus?"},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2364.532","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2364.998","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Adolph Heisler", "start": "2365.812","u": "There I lay four weeks, and then I heard about the transport going to Switzerland. So I reported for it, to go to Switzerland."}        ]
    }
_jsready = true;
var return_val;
switch (String(type)){
        case "transcription":
        return_val = transcription.interview;
        break;
            case "english_translation":
        return_val = english_translation.interview;
        break;
    }
return return_val;
}
function js_ready(){
    return _jsready;
}
